{
 "id": 34270,
 "name": "Technical Architecture Group",
 "is_closed": false,
 "description": "<p>The TAG is a special working group within the W3C, chartered (under the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/policies/process/#TAG\">W3C Process Document</a>) with stewardship of the Web architecture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As outlined by the <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/policies/process/#tag-role\">Process Document</a>, there are three aspects to this mission:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>to document and build consensus around principles of Web architecture and to interpret and clarify these principles when necessary;</li>\r\n<li>to resolve issues involving general Web architecture brought to the TAG;</li>\r\n<li>to help coordinate cross-technology architecture developments inside and outside W3C.</li>\r\n</ul>",
